gar"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"150 g caster sugar, plus an extra 1 teaspoon for dressing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 pears (approx. 150 g - see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"5 black peppercorns"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 dried bay leaf"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp mustard seeds"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 star anise"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp salt, plus extra to season"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g grapeseed oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp french mustard"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"ground black pepper, to season"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g radicchio, leaves separated"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g pecans, roasted and roughly chopped (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g Gorgonzola cheese, cut into pieces (see Tips)"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","3521.2 kJ \/ 838.4 kcal","18.6 g","89.2 g","42.9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["You can find burghul in most supermarkets and health food stores. Be sure to purchase fine burghul, as it will cook faster.","Use a firm variety of pear, such as Bosc, for this recipe. Pear should be ripe, but firm.","You can replace the pecans and Gorgonzola with any nuts and cheese of choice.","You can store any leftover pickling liquid in a sealable container in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. Use in salad dressings or to pickle vegetables of choice."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}